listings.title: Williamsburg/Greenpoint Thrift, Vintage, & Homegoods Sale!
listings.description:
March 18th & 19th | 11am - 4pm  

Location to be announced on March 18th on our Instagram @plumppopup OR DM me for address!  

- Women's Clothing + Shoes
- Handmade Art 
- Home goods 
- Jewelry 
- Custom Hats 
- Mens Clothing + Shoes 

We are Williamsburg/Greenpoint residents, artists, and creatives who believe in the value of community. We’ve come together as neighbors to create the most epic, not-your-average stoop sale pop-up in Williamsburg NYC, because we believe in community and bringing our neighbors and friends together. 

Our Plump Pop-up idea was created through a simple idea to have a moving-out garage/stoop sale. Since we are all artists, thrifters, and designers, we came up with the idea to share our lives with our creative neighborhood by hosting a curated pop-up inside our historical Williamsburg building.  The location of the event is housed in one of Williamsburg’s oldest buildings that’s about to go to ruin through new development within the coming months. As residents of this could-be historical landmark in Williamsburg, we want to keep the spirit alive and bring artists, creatives, and neighbors together to repurpose thrifted finds, handmade art & furniture, and so much more with each of you– and what better way to do that than in THE thrifting neighborhood of NYC? 


Follow us on IG @plumppopup to keep up with all the details surrounding this fun event #notyouraveragestoopsale

listings.title: ReCycle Bikes of Staten Island - Bicycle Redistribution Program
listings.description:
* ReCycle collects, repairs and redistributes  pre-owned adult and children's bicycles at bargain prices that anyone can afford.   This puts self-sustaining modes of transport back into the community and out of our landfills. 

To date we have repurposed and redistributed over 300 bikes since 2020.  At an average weight of 30 pounds per bike that's over 9,000 pounds of metal waste that was put back into use, protecting our environment and contributing to the ZERO emissions initiative. 

And as a positive side effect, you get some much needed exercise we can all use. 

Adult bikes start at $59 (24 - 28 inch).  

Kids bikes start at $45 (20 Inch). 

Children's bikes start at $25 (18 inches and below - not shown)

All bikes are made ride ready.  Choose a bike and request more information and pictures. 

*first picture is generic and for illustration purpose only.

listings.title: Custom PC Builds
listings.description:
Need a PC built? I'm your guy. I have countless builds under my belt with experience from basic builds to complex custom water looped builds with soft tubing. My builds are clean and I try to keep the wire management as neat as possible. Every build comes with a retail copy of Windows 10/11 and is stress tested for stability and to make sure everything works. 

I can help you pick your parts for an optimal build depending on your needs and budget, keep you updated on the build, and even deliver within a certain distance. If shipping is required, you will pay for all packaging/shipping fees. Turn around time is about 1-4 days after I receive all the parts depending on complexity of build. I charge anywhere from $100-$150 for basic builds and $200-$400 for complex builds. Check the pics for some of the builds I've done in the past. Feel free to message me with any questions.
